{
  "stem": "13817.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You had to have special ID cards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You had to wear your star.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "On the streetcar, you only could stand on the back-- in the platform on the back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Your rations-- at that time, Germany already had shortages on food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The rations for the Jews were half what the-- what the other population had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The Jews didn't get any ration cards for clothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But like I said, my mother before, she had friends in that little town, and there was kind of a black market going on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And some of their friends would bring extra food to our place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so we, we really had-- we didn't feel the emergency as bad as, as, as a lot of other people did.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because living in that little town, all the farmers had butter, had eggs, had milk.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We would get-- they would kill cattles, and we would get some meat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So this was the way we lived then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then this-- we lived in the Juden apartment with a other lady with two boys.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Her husband was a Polish citizen, and he was already shipped to Poland in '39.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He-- that is where this whole deal of the so-called Kristallnacht started.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "This-- his parents were in that same situation there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And then till October, October 31 or 30, I think, in 1941, we got-- two days before, we got a notice that we had to be at the railway station.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We could take 100 marks, which was nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "You could take one suitcase, and you could take bedding, but only as much as you could carry.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "You had to report to the station in two days.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
